[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: MIL-STD-498 STP (Software Test Plan)

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1. Scope

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.1 Identification

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-001
TITLE: Test Plan Identification
STATEMENT: This document shall be identified as the Software Test Plan (STP) for the Satellite Communication Management System (SCMS), version 1.0.
RATIONALE: Proper document identification ensures configuration management and test traceability.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.2 System overview

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-002
TITLE: Test Scope Overview
STATEMENT: The test plan shall cover comprehensive testing of the SCMS including unit testing, integration testing, system testing, security testing, and performance testing.
RATIONALE: Comprehensive test scope ensures system quality and reliability validation.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.3 Document overview

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-003
TITLE: Test Plan Structure
STATEMENT: This document shall be organized into sections covering test approach, test environment, test procedures, test data, and test reporting requirements.
RATIONALE: Structured organization facilitates test execution and stakeholder communication.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.4 Relationship to other plans

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-004
TITLE: Plan Integration
STATEMENT: This test plan shall align with the project management plan, quality assurance plan, and risk management plan to ensure coordinated project execution.
RATIONALE: Plan integration ensures consistent project approach and resource utilization.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 2. Referenced documents

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-005
TITLE: Test References
STATEMENT: The test plan shall reference the SRS, SDD, and system requirements documents to ensure complete requirement coverage and validation.
RATIONALE: Test references ensure alignment with system requirements and design specifications.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3. Software test environment

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-006
TITLE: Test Infrastructure
STATEMENT: The test environment shall include dedicated test servers, network equipment, satellite simulators, and monitoring tools to support comprehensive testing.
RATIONALE: Adequate test infrastructure ensures realistic testing conditions and reliable results.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-007
TITLE: Test Tools
STATEMENT: The test environment shall include automated testing tools, performance monitoring software, security testing tools, and test data management systems.
RATIONALE: Appropriate test tools enable efficient test execution and comprehensive coverage.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4. Test identification

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.1 General information

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-008
TITLE: Test Strategy
STATEMENT: The test strategy shall employ a risk-based approach with automated testing for regression, manual testing for usability, and specialized testing for security and performance.
RATIONALE: Risk-based test strategy optimizes resource utilization and defect detection.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.2 Planned tests

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-009
TITLE: Unit Testing
STATEMENT: Unit testing shall be performed on individual software components with minimum 90% code coverage and automated test execution for continuous integration.
RATIONALE: Unit testing ensures component reliability and facilitates early defect detection.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-010
TITLE: Integration Testing
STATEMENT: Integration testing shall validate component interactions, API functionality, and data flow between system modules with automated test suites.
RATIONALE: Integration testing ensures system component compatibility and communication reliability.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-011
TITLE: System Testing
STATEMENT: System testing shall validate end-to-end functionality, user workflows, and system performance under realistic operational conditions.
RATIONALE: System testing ensures complete system validation and user acceptance readiness.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-012
TITLE: Security Testing
STATEMENT: Security testing shall include penetration testing, vulnerability assessment, and security controls validation to ensure system protection.
RATIONALE: Security testing is critical for military systems to ensure protection against threats.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-013
TITLE: Performance Testing
STATEMENT: Performance testing shall validate system response times, throughput, scalability, and resource utilization under expected and peak load conditions.
RATIONALE: Performance testing ensures system meets performance requirements and operational demands.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-014
TITLE: Usability Testing
STATEMENT: Usability testing shall evaluate user interface effectiveness, navigation efficiency, and user satisfaction with representative user groups.
RATIONALE: Usability testing ensures system accessibility and user adoption success.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5. Test schedules

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-015
TITLE: Test Timeline
STATEMENT: The test schedule shall allocate sufficient time for each test phase with appropriate milestones, deliverables, and stakeholder reviews.
RATIONALE: Realistic test schedule ensures adequate testing and project timeline adherence.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-016
TITLE: Test Phases
STATEMENT: Test phases shall include unit testing (2 weeks), integration testing (3 weeks), system testing (4 weeks), and acceptance testing (2 weeks) with appropriate overlap.
RATIONALE: Structured test phases ensure systematic validation and quality assurance.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 6. Test requirements traceability

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-017
TITLE: Requirements Coverage
STATEMENT: All system requirements shall be traceable to specific test cases with coverage metrics and validation criteria to ensure complete requirement verification.
RATIONALE: Requirements traceability ensures complete system validation and quality assurance.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 7. Notes

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: STP-018
TITLE: Test Notes
STATEMENT: This test plan shall be maintained under configuration control with version history and change tracking to ensure test consistency and traceability.
RATIONALE: Document maintenance ensures test accuracy and stakeholder communication.

[/SECTION]
